#rstats {vapour} key issue the difference of warp-read and RasterIO-read

warp: specify extent (xmin,xmax,ymin,ymax) and dimension

RasterIO specify offset+window to read, so the output extent is *pixel-aligned* - making the UI quite different to warp (both can use extent /1) https://t.co/l9fSRb51A1

but because of the alignment requirement the xmin,xmax,ymin,ymax of the output might not be the same as what the user input (we like to be flexible), so that needs modification 

OR, just *always use warp* ... but covering options is a goal :)
